title: BREAKING: Norway wants say on Brexit talks to influence trade negotiations
text:
BREAKING: Norway wants say on Brexit talks to influence trade negotiations BREAKING: Norway wants say on Brexit talks to influence trade negotiations NORWAY has said it would like to be included in any transitional Brexit talks between the UK and EU. PUBLISHED: 13:35, Tue, Feb 21, 2017 | UPDATED: 13:52, Tue, Feb 21, 2017 GETTY Norway wants to be part of trade negotiations 
“We would like to have the possibility to be included in EU-UK arrangements concerning the internal market, permanent as well as transitional," the Norwegian EEA and EU minister, Frank Bakke-Jensen, said in a speech to EU ambassadors in Oslo. 
The comments come just weeks after the country’s Prime Minister Erna Solberg predicted Britain would opt for a hard Brexit, and would resist buckling under EU pressure. Related articles
